  <name>rproc</name>
  <summary>Resource and process monitor for Linux</summary>
  <developer id="io.github.trystan_sa">
    <name>Trystan Sarrade</name>
  </developer>
  <description>
    <p>
      rproc is a resource and process monitor for Linux, inspired by the
      Windows 11 Task Manager. It shows live CPU, memory, disk, network
      and GPU usage along with the full process tree.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Processes: CPU, memory, disk I/O, threads, status. Sort, filter, kill.</li>
      <li>Performance: live charts for CPU (global + per-core), memory, disks, network, GPU.</li>
      <li>Startup: XDG autostart entries and enabled systemd units.</li>
      <li>Services: systemctl system and user units.</li>
      <li>Adjustable refresh rate.</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
